<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-12-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="426" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d426">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-15"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                    1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. White reports that he has just had an interview with the minister
                            for foreign affairs; that members of the Government are scattered in the
                            country, and no reply to Venezuelan proposal is possible to-day; that
                            there will be a meeting of the cabinet on the 16th instant, after which
                            Mr. White expects to see the minister for foreign affairs.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>